===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|been||to be|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|beon|bēon|to be, become|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|beunan|to be, exist, come to be, become|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰew-|to grow, become, come into being, appear|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|binne||are|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|ben||am|lang=nl}}, Low German ''bün'' ("am"), {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|bin||am|lang=de}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|buan|būan|to live, wone|lang=ang}}. Irregular forms are inherited from the {{etyl|ang}} compound verb {{term|beon-wesan|bēon-wesan|lang=ang}}.

